 response properties with a short probe.
 Other studies using paired pulse protocols 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Cao:2016jl"

\end_inset

 found that responses to brief pulses of odorant reduced gain on timescales
 as brief as 500 ms, which is close to the timescale of the neural response
 to odors 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Martelli:2013it,Kim:2010ds,Nagel:2011jj"

\end_inset

.
 Similar fast timescales of gain control have been observed in the visual
